'cause he can't get out
of his own way,

10:32.432 --> 10:36.167
And i am tired of his problems
being our problems.

10:36.169 --> 10:39.070
I'm not in this for
the bullshit rock star stuff.

10:39.072 --> 10:40.772
I ain't in it
for the limos.

10:40.774 --> 10:44.909
I'm in it to make music,
great music with you.

10:44.911 --> 10:46.945
Let's cut him loose.

10:46.947 --> 10:49.748
[sighs]

10:49.750 --> 10:52.017
We'll give him
one more chance.

10:52.019 --> 10:56.021
Oh, those eyes could
convince me of anything.

10:56.023 --> 10:59.991
(waitress)
would you or your dad
like some more coffee?

10:59.993 --> 11:02.227
Would you like
some more coffee, dad?

11:03.330 --> 11:04.362
[slurps]

11:04.364 --> 11:05.330
(flash)
i dig it, cool.

11:05.332 --> 11:06.364
Song order's dope.

11:06.366 --> 11:07.499
Where you want
my solos?

11:07.501 --> 11:09.200
Every song that has
an asterisk,

11:09.202 --> 11:11.670
And then you do
an extended jam on<i> animal.</i>

11:11.672 --> 11:12.804
Where is my drum solo?

11:12.806 --> 11:13.805
What?

11:13.807 --> 11:14.806
8,000 people, yo,

11:14.808 --> 11:15.974
I toured with the pogues.

11:15.976 --> 11:17.609
8,000 people want
two things:

11:17.611 --> 11:19.611
Beer and drum solos.

11:19.613 --> 11:22.447
Gaga--18,000 people:
Buckets of beer,

11:22.449 --> 11:24.215
Not one drum solo.

11:24.217 --> 11:26.151
He gets a drum solo;
i want a bass solo.

11:26.153 --> 11:27.786
What is this?
1974?

11:27.788 --> 11:29.454
Nobody's getting solos
on anything, okay?

11:29.456 --> 11:30.722
Jesus christ, guys.
Hey!

11:30.724 --> 11:31.823
(ira)
hey!

11:31.825 --> 11:34.225
Show sold out
in seven hours.

11:34.227 --> 11:35.393
- Oh!
- Are you kidding me?

11:35.395 --> 11:36.628
- No!
- Seven hours!

11:36.630 --> 11:38.663
- Are you kidding me?
- Wow.

11:38.665 --> 11:41.466
I got you guys
a one-of-a-kind tour bus,

11:41.468 --> 11:43.735
Fully rigged out
as a nightclub.

11:43.737 --> 11:45.203
- Whoo!
- Dude!

11:45.205 --> 11:46.404
Okay?
First-class flights, okay?

11:46.406 --> 11:47.839
- Yes.
- Awesome.

11:47.841 --> 11:50.642
Our own floor
in a five-star hotel.

11:50.644 --> 11:52.143
Wow.

11:52.145 --> 11:53.344
Afghan whigs only got
regular rooms

11:53.346 --> 11:54.345
When they did brussels.

11:54.347 --> 11:55.580
This is awesome, man.

11:55.582 --> 11:57.749
(ira)
okay, couple last-minute things.

11:57.751 --> 12:00.585
The rider--what do you guys
want backstage?

12:00.587 --> 12:02.721
I want the same thing
i got with gaga:

12:02.723 --> 12:05.323
Two room-temperature
fiji waters;

12:05.325 --> 12:07.492
Seedless grapes, white;
and a little brie.

12:07.494 --> 12:09.227
(rehab)
what the hell, dude?

12:09.229 --> 12:11.663
You getting ready to play
a rock gig or the [...] cello?

12:11.665 --> 12:13.164
(johnny)
yeah, man, we just sold out
a goddamn arena.

12:13.166 --> 12:14.532
We got to have a rider
that reflects

12:14.534 --> 12:16.167
Our newfound
rock star status.

12:16.169 --> 12:18.069
(johnny)
i want four bottles of

12:18.071 --> 12:21.206
Asande grande elite vodka
by christophe cheveux.

12:21.208 --> 12:22.674
What is that?

12:22.676 --> 12:24.109
$3,000 a bottle, baby.
That's what that is.

12:24.111 --> 12:25.944
Each bottle is
individually adorned

12:25.946 --> 12:28.747
With diamonds chosen by the
famed french jeweler himself.

12:28.749 --> 12:31.182
Okay, very elegant,
very tasteful.

12:31.184 --> 12:33.351
I'm also gonna need
a batman bong.

12:33.353 --> 12:34.919
(bam bam)
i want 12 filet mignons,

12:34.921 --> 12:37.255
In a box,
like meat doughnuts.

12:37.257 --> 12:38.623
(rehab)
no, it's been done, bam.

12:38.625 --> 12:39.924
Meat loaf had that
on his rider.

12:39.926 --> 12:41.292
I think that's how
he got his name.

12:41.294 --> 12:42.527
Everything on our rider

12:42.529 --> 12:44.195
Has to blow away
other bands' riders,

12:44.197 --> 12:45.797
So when they hear about it,
it really blows their minds.

12:45.799 --> 12:46.798
I want 27 peaches.

12:46.800 --> 12:48.299
- Why?
- Why not?

12:48.301 --> 12:50.368
Okay, i want a masseuse
that looks like johnny depp.

12:50.370 --> 12:51.636
(johnny)
that's a great idea.

12:51.638 --> 12:53.138
Lookalike masseuses
for everybody.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.539
I want one that looks like
lana del rey.

12:54.541 --> 12:55.940
I want melissa mccarthy--

12:55.942 --> 12:57.876
The actual melissa mccarthy,
the big one.

12:57.878 --> 12:59.978
(rehab)
okay, i want these new pills
they have in belgium

12:59.980 --> 13:01.312
That the fda
hasn't yet approved:

13:01.314 --> 13:03.615
Achievium, accelevate,

13:03.617 --> 13:04.816
And something
called takenderal.

13:04.818 --> 13:05.917
What do they do?

13:05.919 --> 13:07.252
[chuckles]
i have no idea.

13:07.254 --> 13:08.319
That's part of the fun.

13:08.321 --> 13:10.388
I also want an iguana.

13:10.390 --> 13:11.389
Why?

13:11.391 --> 13:12.824
Because i can.

13:12.826 --> 13:14.492
If he's getting an iguana,
i want a snake.

13:14.494 --> 13:15.760
No, dude, snakes
eat iguanas.

13:15.762 --> 13:17.095
Yeah, circle of life,
dude.

13:17.097 --> 13:18.663
Hey, listen, if you're
getting a snake,

13:18.665 --> 13:20.398
You got to get
a 16-foot-long snake at least,

13:20.400 --> 13:23.101
Because the backstage rider
record for a backstage snake

13:23.103 --> 13:24.769
Is 15 feet that nikki sixx
had on his rider.

13:24.771 --> 13:26.771
- That's right.
- This guy is a savant.

13:26.773 --> 13:28.239
You guys,
this is ridiculous.

13:28.241 --> 13:29.941
Flash and i talked about this
this morning--

13:29.943 --> 13:31.576
Priorities, dad, okay?

13:31.578 --> 13:34.412
We are being handed
a huge, huge opportunity here.

13:34.414 --> 13:35.847
Instead of focusing
on the music,

13:35.849 --> 13:37.282
All you care about

13:37.284 --> 13:38.950
Is the rock star bullshit
side of things.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.251
I mean, really,
you want a snake?

13:40.253 --> 13:41.486
And what do you want,
an iguana?

13:41.488 --> 13:42.620
What's next?
A goddamn owl?

13:42.622 --> 13:43.788
It's stupid.

13:43.790 --> 13:45.423
Do you know what
i want backstage?

13:45.425 --> 13:48.993
I want some lemon tea
with honey. Why?

13:48.995 --> 13:51.696
Because i plan on
singing my best, okay?

13:51.698 --> 13:54.132
Giving the audience what
they paid to come and see--

13:54.134 --> 13:56.134
A great and unforgettable
live show

13:56.136 --> 13:58.136
That leaves them
wanting more.

13:58.138 --> 14:00.872
That's what my father told me
was the most important thing.

14:03.777 --> 14:05.877
She's absolutely right,
guys.

14:08.315 --> 14:10.982
Yeah, she is.

14:10.984 --> 14:12.650
I want an owl.

14:12.652 --> 14:15.286
I want the biggest owl
in belgium backstage, okay?

14:15.288 --> 14:16.955
They have a belgian owl
brand of whisky there.

14:16.957 --> 14:18.056
- It's 92 proof.
- Oh, we got to get that.

14:18.058 --> 14:19.457
I want four bottles
of that.

14:19.459 --> 14:20.625
- That's a great idea.
[laughter]

14:26.199 --> 14:27.165
[owl squawks]

14:27.167 --> 14:30.168
[rock music]

14:30.170 --> 14:34.639
♪ ♪

14:34.641 --> 14:37.375
[bubbling]

14:37.377 --> 14:39.377
Yo, babe,

14:39.379 --> 14:41.212
Take it easy
with that belgian blue.

14:41.214 --> 14:43.214
That's, like,
the strongest weed in europe.

14:43.216 --> 14:45.516
You guys think
a crown of thorns is too much?

14:45.518 --> 14:46.818
[exhales forcefully]

14:46.820 --> 14:48.353
(ira)
how's everybody doing?

14:48.355 --> 14:50.021
(bam bam)
did you measure
the snake?

14:50.023 --> 14:51.823
- Yeah, it's 16 1/2 feet.
- Oh, cool.

14:51.825 --> 14:53.358
(ira)
so sven,
the teleprompter guy,

14:53.360 --> 14:55.360
He wants to know how large
you want your lyrics to be.

14:55.362 --> 14:56.694
He says neil young used
the biggest size

14:56.696 --> 14:57.729
When he was here.

14:57.731 --> 14:59.030
Neil young's, like, 90.

14:59.032 --> 14:59.998
I don't need
a teleprompter, okay?

15:00.000 --> 15:01.199
Dad, you never know.

15:01.201 --> 15:02.200
Honey, i know.
I know.

15:02.202 --> 15:03.568
Listen, guys,

15:03.570 --> 15:06.337
I want to tell
you guys something.

15:12.946 --> 15:16.080
And i don't remember
what exactly--hang on.

15:16.082 --> 15:17.882
- Jesus christ.
- All right, all right.

15:17.884 --> 15:19.017
(ira)
no more booze
or bong hits.

15:19.019 --> 15:20.418
We got a two-hour show
to do here.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.253
Re, any of those pills
provide a little pick-me-up,

15:22.255 --> 15:23.721
Make your brain focus?

15:23.723 --> 15:25.556
Oh, yeah, i took
one of each of 'em.

15:25.558 --> 15:27.625
Right now, you are coming in
in 3-d, baby.

15:27.627 --> 15:29.093
(johnny)
okay, wait a minute.

15:29.095 --> 15:30.395
I totally remember
what i was gonna say.

15:30.397 --> 15:31.562
Okay.

15:31.564 --> 15:32.530
[inhales]

15:32.532 --> 15:35.233
I want to say, guys,

15:35.235 --> 15:37.201
You know, we're getting
a second chance here,

15:37.203 --> 15:38.603
And it's not something

15:38.605 --> 15:41.039
That happens to a lot of people,
you know?

15:41.041 --> 15:42.740
The gods of rock and roll
are smiling on us,

15:42.742 --> 15:44.075
And now we have a chance

15:44.077 --> 15:46.077
To be what
we could have been,

15:46.079 --> 15:48.379
What we should have been,
you know,

15:48.381 --> 15:49.747
And what we're gonna be,

15:49.749 --> 15:51.916
Which is the greatest
rock and roll band

15:51.918 --> 15:53.785
On the face
of the planet.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.787
And i just want to tell
you guys, you know,

15:55.789 --> 15:58.589
It's not just gigi,
you know?

15:58.591 --> 16:04.262
I really consider you guys,
like, my family, you know?

16:04.264 --> 16:06.197
Been having this...

16:08.401 --> 16:10.902
Who ate one of my peaches?
God damn it.

16:10.904 --> 16:12.470
Should have gave me
the drum solo.

16:12.472 --> 16:14.005
- You mother--
- no!

16:14.007 --> 16:15.773
- Hey, hey, hey!
- We were having a nice moment!

16:15.775 --> 16:17.175
[all shouting]

16:17.177 --> 16:18.676
Everybody, everybody,
this is it! This is it!

16:18.678 --> 16:20.144
Got all kinds of food
you could have eaten.

16:20.146 --> 16:21.579
- They love drum solos!
- Everybody, come on!

16:21.581 --> 16:22.647
- Calm down!
- We were having a nice moment!

16:22.649 --> 16:24.182
- Asshole.
- This is it!

16:24.184 --> 16:26.517
- Let's go.
- Let's go. Let's go.

16:26.519 --> 16:28.019
[dramatic percussion]

16:28.021 --> 16:30.955
[muffled cheers and applause]

16:30.957 --> 16:32.357
(male announcer)
and welcome...

16:32.359 --> 16:34.525
The heathens!

16:34.527 --> 16:38.129
[cheers and applause]

16:38.131 --> 16:41.099
[lively rock music]

16:41.101 --> 16:45.203
♪ ♪

16:45.205 --> 16:46.337
♪ uh ♪

16:46.339 --> 16:49.841
♪ ♪

16:49.843 --> 16:52.176
♪ let go of my soul ♪

16:52.178 --> 16:54.112
That's why i love
this guy.

16:54.114 --> 16:56.647
♪ let me up
so i can breathe ♪

16:56.649 --> 16:57.949
Born to be a rock star.

16:57.951 --> 16:59.350
♪ ♪

16:59.352 --> 17:03.821
♪ got to find
some kind of cover ♪

17:03.823 --> 17:06.124
♪ from this hold
you have on me ♪

17:06.126 --> 17:08.359
♪ ♪

17:08.361 --> 17:13.197
♪ i'm gonna get
right over you ♪

17:13.199 --> 17:15.700
♪ or i'm gonna die trying ♪

17:15.702 --> 17:18.536
♪ ♪

17:18.538 --> 17:19.570
♪ uh ♪

17:19.572 --> 17:21.839
[erratic drum solo]

17:21.841 --> 17:24.809
[cheers and applause]

17:24.811 --> 17:30.982
♪ ♪

17:30.984 --> 17:33.384
[music whirring and slowing]

17:33.386 --> 17:36.487
[muffled cheers and applause]

17:44.364 --> 17:47.365
[distorted whooshing]

17:47.367 --> 17:51.669
[owl shrieking]

17:51.671 --> 17:53.504
[snake hissing]

17:53.506 --> 17:54.672
Snake!

17:54.674 --> 17:56.074
Snake!

17:56.076 --> 17:58.209
[cheers and applause]

17:58.211 --> 18:00.711
♪ ♪

18:00.713 --> 18:02.280
Who let the animals
out of the cages?

18:02.282 --> 18:04.048
- What?
- The animals are downstairs.

18:04.050 --> 18:05.383
- They are?
- Yes. Are you okay?

18:05.385 --> 18:06.684
- No.
- You got to go back out there.

18:06.686 --> 18:08.386
No, i can't go back
out there.

18:08.388 --> 18:09.520
You're fine.
You're fine. You're fine.

18:09.522 --> 18:10.688
No, no, no.
No, i can't do it.

18:10.690 --> 18:12.190
Honey, you--
you got to go out there.

18:12.192 --> 18:20.331
♪ ♪

18:32.879 --> 18:35.279
[drumsticks tapping]

18:35.281 --> 18:38.249
[mellow rock music]

18:38.251 --> 18:45.056
♪ ♪

18:45.058 --> 18:47.391
♪ i'm gonna drink
all night ♪

18:47.393 --> 18:51.562
♪ until you fade away ♪

18:51.564 --> 18:53.397
♪ yes, i am ♪

18:53.399 --> 18:55.333
♪ ♪

18:55.335 --> 18:56.767
♪ you walk and you talk ♪

18:56.769 --> 19:00.571
♪ and my pain
will all be erased ♪

19:00.573 --> 19:02.573
♪ yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

19:02.575 --> 19:05.376
♪ everything you ever said ♪

19:12.952 --> 19:13.985
- Whoo!
- Go, driver, go!

19:13.987 --> 19:16.254
Gigi, what a show!
Gigi!

19:16.256 --> 19:18.322
(flash)
hey, what's your problem,
johnny?

19:18.324 --> 19:20.358
Bam bam, man, with
your stupid goddamn drum solo,

19:20.360 --> 19:22.093
That's what really
threw me off.

19:22.095 --> 19:24.262
They loved the drum solo,
asshole.

19:24.264 --> 19:25.630
Chick in the front row

19:25.632 --> 19:27.098
Showed me her tits
at the end of it.

19:27.100 --> 19:28.499
(gigi)
yeah, while you were onstage

19:28.501 --> 19:30.134
Doing your stupid little
invisible snake dance...

19:30.136 --> 19:31.335
That's because the pills

19:31.337 --> 19:32.970
That rehab gave me
made me hallucinate.

19:32.972 --> 19:34.839
[laughs]
i know.

19:34.841 --> 19:37.041
Okay, no more unapproved pills
or blue weed.

19:37.043 --> 19:38.342
That's what did it.

19:38.344 --> 19:40.011
That's right.
That's what did it.

19:40.013 --> 19:41.145
- That's what did it, yeah.
- I know. It is, baby.

19:41.147 --> 19:42.280
- Yep, yep.
- Bullshit.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.482
We know what it was.
Huh?

19:44.484 --> 19:46.517
Don't go indulging this guy's
goddamn victim complex.

19:46.519 --> 19:47.985
Get real.

19:47.987 --> 19:49.053
I told you
he was out to get me.

19:49.055 --> 19:50.188
It's unbelievable.

19:50.190 --> 19:51.556
(flash)
hey, this was the last gig

19:51.558 --> 19:52.657
For the heathens, okay?

19:52.659 --> 19:53.624
So i hope you enjoyed

19:53.626 --> 19:55.293
Your final onstage meltdown.

19:55.295 --> 19:57.461
Heathens' last gig
forever.

19:57.463 --> 19:59.664
First gig
for the assassins!

19:59.666 --> 20:01.132
You're gone,

20:01.134 --> 20:03.000
And you are off team assassin,
my friend.

20:03.002 --> 20:04.402
You're not taking us
down with you.

20:04.404 --> 20:05.836
What?

20:05.838 --> 20:07.838
We've been making
new plans for the band.

20:07.840 --> 20:10.007
(ira)
what should have
happened in 1992,

20:10.009 --> 20:11.909
What could have
happened in '94

20:11.911 --> 20:14.145
And '96 or 2003--

20:14.147 --> 20:15.813
Would have been
the same result,

20:15.815 --> 20:18.416
Johnny taking us
to the edge of success

20:18.418 --> 20:20.484
And then hitting
the self-destruct button.

20:20.486 --> 20:22.653
Team assassin can't
afford that anymore.

20:22.655 --> 20:23.688
Hold on.

20:23.690 --> 20:25.223
Gigi,

20:25.225 --> 20:28.025
Do you want
your father off...

20:28.027 --> 20:29.627
Team assassin?

20:32.065 --> 20:33.864
I just got a text
from our promoters.

20:33.866 --> 20:36.033
They want the assassins back
for another show this fall.

20:36.035 --> 20:38.035
Two shows this fall.

20:38.037 --> 20:39.670
He loved you, gigi.

20:39.672 --> 20:42.573
All right, they want to know
what color t-shirts we want.

20:42.575 --> 20:44.709
They think they can really move
a lot of assassins merchandise.

20:44.711 --> 20:45.676
(ira)
go high, bro.

20:45.678 --> 20:47.111
[hands slap]

20:47.113 --> 20:48.246
(flash)
[grunts] gi, tell him he's gone.

20:48.248 --> 20:49.847
Tell him what
we talked about.

20:49.849 --> 20:52.817
What did you talk about?
Honey?

20:57.357 --> 21:00.925
Dad, you're off
team assassin...

21:00.927 --> 21:03.694
Because you've just been
promoted to team gigi.

21:03.696 --> 21:06.464
- You're all on team gigi.
- [laughs]

21:06.466 --> 21:07.865
Dad stays on.
You guys keep cowriting.

21:07.867 --> 21:09.567
I work closer
with the two of you.

21:09.569 --> 21:11.769
I learn more about the craft
and about songwriting,

21:11.771 --> 21:13.638
And, dad, i'm taking you
to see a shrink.

21:13.640 --> 21:15.640
No, no, honey, i--i'm not--
i don't have to--

21:15.642 --> 21:17.275
(gigi)
oh, no, no,
no, no, no.

21:17.277 --> 21:19.410
We need to solve my dad's
psychological problems

21:19.412 --> 21:20.778
So he stops screwing us up.

21:20.780 --> 21:22.413
And you all are coming
into the sessions.

21:22.415 --> 21:23.914
- Oh, oh!
- I'm not going to a shrink.

21:23.916 --> 21:25.750
Excuse me!
Excuse me! Excuse me!

21:25.752 --> 21:27.551
Hey!
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

21:27.553 --> 21:30.254
This band is
so freakin' dysfunctional,

21:30.256 --> 21:32.623
It makes metallica look like
the goddamn jonas brothers.

21:32.625 --> 21:34.792
Ira, you can tell the promoter
we'll be taking the gigs.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.294
Gi, let's go
talk about this--

21:36.296 --> 21:37.928
All t-shirts, ira,
and promotional materials

21:37.930 --> 21:39.297
Including the marquee
will read

21:39.299 --> 21:40.631
"gigi and the assassins."

21:40.633 --> 21:41.899
Okay, now, the next time
we come back here,

21:41.901 --> 21:43.234
I'm gonna need
a couple things.

21:43.236 --> 21:44.502
- You writing this down?
- Yep.

21:44.504 --> 21:45.803
Four bottles of

21:45.805 --> 21:47.138
Krug clos d'ambonnay
champagne

21:47.140 --> 21:48.906
In the black gift boxes,

21:48.908 --> 21:50.508
Six dozen white roses,

21:50.510 --> 21:52.943
And a pair of white bone
pearl teardrop earrings

21:52.945 --> 21:54.145
From chopard.

